cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the placement of a UAV-BS and its backhaul link with terrestrial Macro-cell Base Stations (MBSs) to improve network performance and profitability. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with bandwidth allocation to users to maximize the achievable data rate levels. This involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding theory.
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes a strategy to improve profitability by applying price differentiation for different service levels. This involves game theory concepts such as pricing strategies and revenue maximization.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the placement of a UAV-BS and its backhaul link as a system and formulates a Mixed Integer Non-Linear Programming (MINLP) problem to optimize the placement and bandwidth allocation. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the Quality-of-Experience (QoE) requirements of users and proposes multiple data rate options to improve QoE. This falls under the scope of multimedia as QoE is a key factor in multimedia applications.
